    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2246320170" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2246320170" />
    <a title="Greg" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6922605-greg"><img alt="Greg" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1320867217p2/6922605.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2246320170?book_show_action=true">Jan 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Greg" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Greg" href="/user/show/6922605-greg">Greg</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9782070445790" href="/book/show/15907960-berenice">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6922605-greg?shelf=drama">drama</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2246320170" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10405427371501183833">Victor Hugo summarized this play by describing the formula of its acts: Titus, Queen Berenice, he unwilling, her unwilling, and sent away. The formula is based on a quotation from Suetonius, and it was not meant favorably.<br/><br/>The play is based on Berenice, the Queen of Palestine during the reign of the Roman emperor Titus, and explores the tragedy of their relationship. It is a straightforward, realistic play. Titus says, “I feel that without you I cannot live. My heart is straining hard to leave my</span>
  <span id="freeText10405427371501183833" style="display:none">Victor Hugo summarized this play by describing the formula of its acts: Titus, Queen Berenice, he unwilling, her unwilling, and sent away. The formula is based on a quotation from Suetonius, and it was not meant favorably.<br /><br />The play is based on Berenice, the Queen of Palestine during the reign of the Roman emperor Titus, and explores the tragedy of their relationship. It is a straightforward, realistic play. Titus says, “I feel that without you I cannot live. My heart is straining hard to leave my breast; But living’s not the question: I must reign.” It has recovered its reputation since the initial judgment by Racine’s peers, but it is not my favorite. If you love a good tragedy, you will like this.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/6922605-greg?page=1&amp;shelf=read" rel="nofollow noopener">See my other reviews here!</a><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10405427371501183833" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


